<TITLE> Stocks remain in doldrums </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 8 (bdnews24.com)Markets lost for the straight second day on Wednesday as investor participation was at its lowest ebb, said market observers. Market experts said individual investors were refraining from trade due to the recent gloomy trend of the market. "Retail investors are gripped with fear due to the losing trend as well as depressing economic forecasts due to the global financial crisis," said former DSE chief executive Salahuddin Ahmed. The declining turnover reflects poor investor participation, added Ahmed who teaches finance at Dhaka University. The DSE general index witnessed a sharp fall on opening, recovered some losses in the midday sessions followed by another downward curve. The DGEN or general index fell 24.17 points or 0.99 percent, closing on 2414.27. The DSI or all share price index ended on 2005.88, down 18.47 points or 0.91 percent. The blue-chip DSE-20 lost 21.19 points or 1.13 percent to finish on 1851.16. Losers beat gainers 130 to 111 while four issues held steady. Brokerage house officials said banks continued slide from the previous day with insurers and non-bank financial institutions also seeing losses Wednesday. "Mutual funds witnessed a hike while power and energy shares fell on profit taking," an official of Anwar Securities told bdnews24.com. Dhaka Stock Exchange saw 25,880,084 shares worth Tk 4.11 billion changing hands, edging down from Tuesday's Tk 4.35 billion. DSE's top ten by turnover Shinepukur Ceramics topped the board with a turnover of Tk 471.154 million. It rose 9.61 percent to Tk 109.40. Beximco followed, with turnover of Tk 361.784 million, to end 0.85 percent up at Tk 247.20. Summit Power had shares worth Tk 306.454 million traded and edged down 0.55 percent to end on Tk 1218.50. Power Grid Company of Bangladesh ended on Tk 650.75, 0.42 percent. It saw shares worth Tk 180.817 million changing hands. State owned Titas Gas lost 1.42 percent to Tk 485.75 with a turnover of Tk 163.092 million. Among the other scrips on the turnover board Beximco Pharmaceuticals, S Alam Cold Rolled Steels and Eastern Housing Ltd androse on buying pressure. DESCO and Aftab Automobiles fell on profit taking. CSE Indices on the Chittagong Stock Exchange also finished down on losses in insurance, banks and non-banking financial institutions. The CSCX or selective categories index lost 43.12 points or 0.86 percent to close at 4932.12. The CASPI or all share price index ended on 7630.72, falling 55.86 points or 0.72 percent. The CSE-30 blue-chip index shed 48.54 points or 0.84 percent to finish at 5675.70. Of the traded issues, 81 declined, 70 advanced with five scrips unchanged. Turnover on the port city's bourse reached Tk 557.280 million from trading of 5,411,900 sharesdown from Tk 685.190 million the previous day. AIMS 1st mutual fund led in turnover on the CSE, with transactions of Tk 1.032 million followed by Shinepukur Ceramics, Bextex Ltd, Modern Cement and Padma Cement.
